### Requirements

Below is the process for the **Long-Term Injury Exclusion**:

1. Must [waive](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/waivers/) the Player;
2. Apply for cap relief after ‚Äúwaiting period‚Äù, which is:  
   * If 10+ games played in the last Season, apply 1-year anniversary of final game;  
   * If less than 10 games played in the last Season, then apply 60 days after the player‚Äôs last game, or 1-year anniversary of the final game in the _previous_ season;
3. Must be the same Team Player was on when he was injured;
4. Can‚Äôt apply if already applied for DPE;
5. Certified by a physician that the injury is career-ending;
6. If the League grants the relief, the Salary is removed from Team Salary immediately, and the Team is prohibited from resigning the Player.

### Playing Again

If the Player plays 25 games again after the League granted the relief above, the Team Salary for the current Season is included in Team Salary for the original Team, unless ruling was based on ‚Äúmaterially elevated risk.‚Äù The Team may reapply to have the Salary excluded using the same process.

The following Contract types are excluded from Team Salary:

1. [Summer Contracts](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#exhibit9);
