In determining if a Team falls above or below the First or Second Apron, **Apron Team Salary** is used.

Apron Team Salary takes [Team Salary](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/), subtracts applicable [Cap Holds](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/#capholds), and includes the following (click to review details).

1. [Team Salary](#teamsalary) _less_ Cap Holds;
2. [Unlikely Bonuses](#unlikely);
3. [Salary Attributable to 0 to 1 YOS Contracts](#zero);
4. [Potential Additions from Grievances/Settlements](#grievance);
5. [Qualifying Offers/Matches](#qo);
6. [Required Tender](#tender);
7. [Second Round Pick Exception](#second).

### Team Salary

Apron Team Salary includes [Team Salary](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/) after subtracting all applicable [Cap Holds](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/#capholds).

### Unlikely Bonuses

Apron [Team Salary](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/) adds [Unlikely Bonuses](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/compensation/incentivecompensation/#performance), which are not included in the initial calculation of Team Salary.

### 0 to 1 Years of Service Contracts

A Player‚Äôs Salary is _increased_ to [Minimum Salary](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/contractlimitations/) for 2 [YOS](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/#yos) in situations when a Player signs as a Free Agent and has less than 2 YOS, called a **0 to 1 YOS Contract** in the Guide.

A Contract is a 0 to 1 YOS Contract if the following criteria is met:

1. Player signs as a [Free Agent](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/ufa/);
2. Player has 0 or 1 [Years of Service](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/#yos);
3. Player signs a Standard NBA Contract which can include (for purposes of this rule) the following, so long as such were signed as Free Agents:  
   * [Exhibit 10 Contract](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#exhibit10);  
   * [Two-Way Contract](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#twoway) converted to a Standard Contract;  
   * [10-Day Contract](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#tenday).

When a 0 to 1 YOS Contract is signed, you add the difference between his Salary (for [Team Salary](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/) purposes) and the applicable [Minimum Salary](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/contractlimitations/) for a Player with 2 [YOS](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/#yos). In other words, you‚Äôre switching his applicable Minimum Salary for that of a 2 YOS Minimum Salary.

**üèÄ** **Carlsen Salary Adjustment for 0 to 1 YOS Contract**  
In 2024-25, Brenden Carlson signed with the Oklahoma City Thunder for a Minimum Salary Contract in the middle of the season. He had 0 YOS. His Team Salary was a pro-rated $990,895, applicable to a Player with 0 YOS. However, his Apron Salary was $1,787,599, applicable to a Player with 2 YOS.

### Settlements/Grievances

Adjust Apron Team Salary for any amount that _could be_ added to Team Salary as a result of a [Grievance or Settlement](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/teamsalary/#settlements).

### Qualifying Offers and First Refusal Exercise Notices

The _greater of_ (i) [Salary](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/compensation/salary/) plus [Unlikely Bonuses](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/compensation/incentivecompensation/#performance) called for in any oustanding [Qualifying Offer](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#qualifyingoffer) or (ii) the Salary plus Unlikely Bonuses called for in any [First Refusal Exercise Notice](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#rofr) issued with respect to such Player.

### Required Tender

The amount of any outstanding [Required Tender](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/draftrules/#tender).

### Second Round Pick Exception

Any amount that was excluded from Team Salary between 7/1 through 7/30 because the Player signed as a [Second Round Pick Exception](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/salarycap/#second).

