6. Void any transaction violating this provision and claw back any value the Player received;  
   * Exceptions ‚Äì If the Player received Compensation for services already performed and/or Player establishes by a preponderance of the evidence he was unaware of the violation.

The Commissioner may also fine the Team or Team Personnel $1 million without any proceeding before a System Arbitrator.

### Penalties for Player Representatives

If ruling on individual/entity acting on behalf of Player:

1. System Arbitrator must make specific determination;
2. If violation is found and upheld on appeal, it is referred to the NBPA;
3. The violation will be considerd a violation of NBPA regulations;
4. NBPA will impose its own penalty.

The NBPA is to issue a suspension of a _minimum_ 1-year suspension of a Player Agent‚Äôs license.

No adverse inference will be made should the party initiating the proceeding delay in doing so until there was further reason to believe there was a violaiton.

If the transaction triggers the rule, the League may challenge the transaction:

1. League and NBPA select a business valuation expert (Business Expert);
2. Business Expert holds a hearing and makes a determination, with the League holding the burden of proof;
3. The Business Expert‚Äôs decision can be appealed to the System Arbitrator.

The Teams and League are prohibited from agreeing or conspiring to do the following:

1. To negotiate or not to negotiate with any Player;
2. To submit or not to submit an [Offer Sheet](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#offersheet);
3. To offer or not to offer a Player Contract;
4. To exercise or not to exercise [FREN](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#rofr);
5. Discuss the terms of employment for a Player;
6. Disclose an [RFA](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/) is negotiating with a Team.

The following are expressly considered non-collusive actions:

1. CBA negotiations;
2. [Trades](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/trades/);
3. [Sign-and-Trades](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/trades/signandtrade/) or [Extend-and-Trades](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/trades/signandtrade/#extend);
4. [NBA Draft](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/draftrules/) discussions;
5. [League discipline](https://cbaguide.com/governance/conduct/) of a Player;
6. Commissioner disapproval of a Contract.

No Team can fail or refuse to negotiate with a Player for the following reasons:

1. Another Team previously had [Draft Rights](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/draftrules/);
2. Player declined a Player [Option](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/options/);
3. Player becomes a [RFA](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/)/[UFA](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/ufa/);
4. Player is or has been subject to [Right of First Refusal](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#rofr).

The **Grievance Arbitrator** handles all disputes relating to the interpetation of the CBA, UPC, and the Domestic Violence Policy.

The **System Arbitrator** handles disputes relating to the following portions of the CBA and UPC:

1. Definitions;
2. Uniform Player Contract;
3. BRI;
4. Thresholds and applicable rules;
5. The Designated Share;
6. Rookie Scale Contracts;
7. Circumvention;
8. Anti-Collusion;
9. Certification of Contracts;
10. Player Health and Wellness;
11. Confidentiality Violations via Combine;
12. Games Played Requirement;
13. Unauthorized Sponsor Promotion.

A Grievance‚Äìbefore the Grievance Arbitrator‚Äìmay be filed by a Player, Team, the League of the NBPA.

A System Arbitration may only be filed by the League or NBPA.

Teams are not permitted to enter into oral or written agreements (or Trades) during the July Moratorium other than the following:

1. [Rookie Scale Contracts](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/draftpicks/);
2. Contract signed pursuant to [Second Round Pick Exception](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/salarycap/#second);
3. [Required Tenders](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/draftrules/#tender);
4. [Minimum Contracts](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/terms/contractlimitations/);
5. [Two-Way Contracts](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#twoway);
6. Two-Way Conversion Option via [Exhibit 10](https://cbaguide.com/contractanatomy/contracttypes/#exhibit10);
7. [Qualifying Offers](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#qualifyingoffer)/[Maximum Qualifying Offers](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#maximum);
8. [Offer Sheet](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/#offersheet).

A Team cannot begin negotiating with a Player other than as permitted below. If negotiations take place outside of this timeframe, then it is considered **Tampering**.

### UFA and RFA‚Äôs

A Player that will, or could be, a [UFA](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/ufa/) or [RFA](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/signings/rfa/) on July 1st, and finished the Season on the Team‚Äôs [roster](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/rosters/), can begin negotiating with the Team after the NBA Finals.

A UFA and RFA can begin negotiating with any Team on June 30th at 6:00 P.M. ET.

On June 29th at 6:00 P.M. E.T., Teams can communicate with Players for the sole purpose of scheduling a meeting to take place on or after June 30th at 6:00 P.M.

### Rookie Free Agents

A [Rookie Free Agent ](https://cbaguide.com/eligibility/draftrules/)can begin negotiating with Teams following the conclusion of the NBA Draft.

### Extensions & Renegotiations

An [Extension](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/extensions/) of a Contract with more than 1 Season and any Designated Veteran Extension cannot be negotiated during the Regular Season.

A [Renegotiation](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/renegotiations/) cannot be negotiated between March 1st through June 30th.

A Team can begin negotiating an Extension or Renegotiation with a Player after the NBA Finals, if an Extension or Renegotiation can be signed after the Moratorium Period.

Expansion

 A number of rules within the Guide have a nuanced change should an Expansion Team be considered. Rather than mention those nuances within each individual rule, they are provided below.

Exclude Expansion Teams for the first 2 years from calculations of:

1. [Average](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/)[ Player Salary](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/);
2. [Total](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/#totalsalaries)[ Salaries](https://cbaguide.com/definitions/#totalsalaries);
3. [BRI](https://cbaguide.com/finances/#bri) (but include shares of national media revenue);
4. [Salary](https://cbaguide.com/finances/#cap)[ Cap](https://cbaguide.com/finances/#cap).

An Expansion Team will have 66.66% of the normal Salary Cap Threshold in the first year it plays and 80% in the second year.

If an Expansion Team selects a Player in an Expansion Draft, then [waives](https://cbaguide.com/transactions/waivers/) him, the Salary won‚Äôt count toward Team Salary, but will count toward [Minimum Team Salary](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/minimumsalary/) if actually paid.

[Bird](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/salarycap/#bird)[ Rights](https://cbaguide.com/thresholds/salarycap/#bird) do not reset when Expansion Team selects a Player in an Expansion Draft.

Definitions

Average Player Salary ‚Äì Total Salaries (including payments made as penalty being below Minimum Team Salary Threshold), divided by 396. 
* The 396 number is taking the number of Teams (30) and multiplying by 13.2
Base Compensation ‚Äì Compensation other than any Bonuses of any kind. Estimated Average Player Salary (EAPS) ‚Äì 104.5% of the Prior Year‚Äôs Average Player Salary. Incentive Compensation ‚Äì All encompassing definition for three types of incentives permitted in Contracts: 
1. Performance Bonuses (Likely or Unlikely);
2. Physical/Academic Achievements;
3. Promotional Appearances.
Room ‚Äì The extent to which: 
1. Team Salary is less than the Salary Cap, or;
2. Team is entitled to use the following Exceptions:  
   * Disabled Player Exception;  
   * Bi-Annual Exception;  
   * NTMLE;  
   * TMLE;  
   * Room MLE;  
   * Traded Player Exception.
Season ‚Äì Period beginning on the first day of training camp through the last game of the NBA Finals. 
* Unless otherwise stated, when counting Seasons, you count the then-current Season a Contract/Extension is signed (even if 1 day is left in the Year), and you count the Option Year.
* Unless otherwise stated, all calculation of Compensation and Salary will include the Option Year.
Team Affiliate ‚Äì The following are included in Team Affiliate: 
1. Any individual/entity with an ownership interest in the Team;
2. Any (i) individual/entity that (ii) is controlled by or under common control with, (iii) an entity affiliated to the Team or an individual related to the Team;
3. Any (i) individual/entity that (ii) is controlled by or under common control with, (iii) an entity or individual from #2 above;
4. Any entity that someone from #1 or #2 above, either (i) holds more than 5% ownership interests or (ii) particpates/influences in management or operations.
Total Salaries ‚Äì Salaries included in Team Salary, but make the following adjustments: 
1. Include Incentive Compensation actually earned;
2. Exclude Incentive Compensaiton not earned;
3. Include Salary excluded from Team Salary as a Long-Term Injury Exclusion;
4. Include retired player payments;
5. Two-Way Salaries paid;
6. Include Exhibit 10 Bonuses paid;
7. Exclude 50% of Compensation reduced from suspension by the League or Team;
8. Disregard any stretching of Salary (apply Salary prior to Stretch).
Years of Service (YOS) ‚Äì The number of years of NBA service for a Player. If the Player is credited for a service year, then it is added on July 1st the following Salary Cap Year. 

A Player is credited with a YOS for each year he is on an NBA Active or Inactive List for 1+ days during the Regular Season.

A Player will not be credited his YOS under the following circumstances:

1. Withholds services during the Season for 30+ days;
2. RFA does not sign a Contract by March 1st when his QO is extended to March 1st;
3. Commissioner disapproved a Contract.
